# validation-rules

## Core Validation Components

### Attribute Validation (Importance: 85)
- Validates complex attribute constraints including:
  - Enum cardinality (single vs multi-select) 
  - Numeric bounds and integer requirements
  - String length and regex pattern matching
  - Boolean value validation

### Modifier Validation (Importance: 90) 
- Ensures modifiers reference valid metrics and operations
- Validates modifier value calculations against configuration rules
- Enforces stacking rules and priority ordering
- Validates conditional logic attached to modifiers

### Configuration Schema Validation (Importance: 95)
- Validates attribute schemas based on type-specific requirements
- Ensures operations declared in configuration have implementations
- Enforces uniqueness constraints on metrics and attributes
- Validates relationships between attributes and modifiers

## Domain-Specific Validation Rules

### Item Specification Validation (Importance: 88)
- Validates complete item specifications against configuration schema
- Enforces complex attribute combinations and dependencies
- Ensures modifiers comply with item-level constraints

### Enum Validation Rules (Importance: 82)
- Handles single vs multi-select enum validation
- Enforces cardinality constraints
- Validates values against allowed enum sets

### Numeric Constraints (Importance: 80)
- Validates finite numeric values
- Enforces min/max bounds
- Handles integer vs float requirements
- Prevents invalid calculations (NaN, Infinity)

